Handling of message/ACK lost:

Terminologies:
  Expected ACK: ACK with sequence numebr == last ACK heard + 1
  Past ACK: ACK with sequence number <= last ACK heard
  Future ACK: ACK with sequence number > last ACK heard + 1


Sender side
-----------

For blocked send:
  If past (duplicated) ACK is received, just drop it.
  It should be impossible to receive future ACK.

For unblocked send:
  If past ACK is received, just drop it.
  If future ACK is received, handle all past message and ACKed message.

If message send is timeout, flag this session to be timeout.
  Next message should be sent with the IPC_FLAG_SEQ_SYNC flag set.

Receiver side
-------------
  If past message is received, ACK with the last ACK heard.
    Need to store the msg_id of last message then.
  If future message is received, just drop it.



Add handling of future ACK.
  - in ipc_message_done_handler(), if there is a forward jump
    in the sequence number of the ACK, instead of handling the
    ACKed message right away, it will just update the session
    status so next time TX runs ipc_resend_messages(), all the
    old message will be handled in send sequence.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

For local IPC, there is no way to send future ACK since sequence number is
not sent in the ACK!  However, this should not be a problem assuming QNX
is reliable!  We will not support this in local IPC, unless such a need arise
in the future.

